# Qure Context Routing (Always On)

This is the routing layer. Keep context minimal and load only files needed for the current task. **Only use tokens and values defined in Figma-linked rule files.** Do not invent or assume values.

All component rules have been rebuilt from Figma. Token aliases below align with `design-system-tokens.mdc`.

## Global baseline (always active)
- Use design tokens only. Do not hardcode colors, spacing, typography, radii, shadows.
- Theme with `data-theme` on `<html>` (`light` default, `dark` optional).
- Global token aliases (use only these; see design-system-tokens.mdc):
  - Surface: `--bg-base-default`, `--bg-base-secondary`, `--bg-base-tertiary`
  - Text: `--text-base-default`, `--text-base-secondary`, `--text-disabled-default`
  - Brand: `--bg-brand-default`, `--bg-brand-tertiary`, `--text-brand-default`, `--text-brand-on-brand`
  - Border: `--border-base-default`, `--border-base-secondary`, `--border-brand-default`
  - Semantic: `--bg-success-default`, `--bg-warning-default`, `--bg-danger-default`; `--text-success-default`, `--text-warning-default`, `--text-danger-default`; `--border-danger-default`
  - Utilities: `--bg-blanket`, `--bg-scrim`
- If exact token values are needed, load `design-system-tokens.mdc`.
- If dark/light behavior is needed, load `design-system-theming.mdc`.

## Context loading protocol
1. Identify task scope from prompt and edited files.
2. Load only matching component/layout rules from table below.
3. Keep active rules minimal:
   - Component task: baseline + 1 component rule (+ `ds-icons.mdc` only if icon-specific)
   - Page/layout task: baseline + `design-system-composition.mdc` + up to 2 component rules
   - Theming task: baseline + `design-system-theming.mdc` (+ `design-system-tokens.mdc` if values needed)
4. Do not load unrelated component rules.

## Fallback for differently named files (existing repos)
- Do not rely on filename match alone.
- If prompt intent is clear (for example: "build an upgrade dialog"), load rule by intent even if file name is non-standard.
- Use path semantics as secondary hints:
  - `**/components/**`, `**/ui/**`, `**/features/**`, `**/views/**`, `**/screens/**`
- If both filename and prompt are ambiguous, infer from JSX structure:
  - Overlay/backdrop + focus trap + close action -> `ds-modal.mdc`
  - Field label + helper/error text + input control -> `ds-input.mdc`
  - Trigger + menu/options list -> `ds-dropdown.mdc`
  - Expand/collapse chevron + hidden content -> `ds-accordion.mdc`
  - Dismissible banner/toast/inline alert -> `ds-notifications.mdc`

## Router-first behavior
- This file is the entrypoint for context routing.
- Always pick rules by task intent first, then validate with filename/path hints.
- If one rule is insufficient, add at most one adjacent rule (for example `ds-modal.mdc` + `ds-button.mdc`).

## Prompt-to-rule map
- Button/CTA/action -> `ds-button.mdc`
- Modal/dialog/panel/sheet -> `ds-modal.mdc`
- Input/form field/search/password/textarea -> `ds-input.mdc`
- Dropdown/select/menu list -> `ds-dropdown.mdc`
- Date/date picker/calendar -> `ds-datepicker.mdc`
- Checkbox/radio/toggle/switch -> `ds-selection.mdc`
- Card/pricing/review/timer/quote -> `ds-card.mdc`
- Accordion/FAQ/collapse -> `ds-accordion.mdc`
- Avatar/profile group -> `ds-avatar.mdc`
- Navbar/topbar/sidebar/tabs/navigation list -> `ds-navbar.mdc`
- Notification/alert/banner/toast/message -> `ds-notifications.mdc`
- Tag/chip/label/pill -> `ds-tags.mdc`
- Filter chip / toggle chip -> `ds-filterchip.mdc`
- Badge/status indicator -> `ds-badges.mdc`
- Tooltip/hint/popover tip -> `ds-tooltip.mdc`
- Icon selection/sizing/color/accessibility -> `ds-icons.mdc`
- Typography scale/headings/text styles -> `ds-typography.mdc`
- List/data list/feed rows -> `ds-lists.mdc`
- Section assembly/page scaffolding/dashboard/chat layout -> `design-system-sections-guide.mdc` + `design-system-composition.mdc`
- Theme/color-mode/dark mode/light mode -> `design-system-theming.mdc`
- Token definitions/aliases/raw values -> `design-system-tokens.mdc`

## Conflict resolution priority
1. Component-specific rules (`ds-*.mdc`)
2. Theming rules (`design-system-theming.mdc`)
3. Token source of truth (`design-system-tokens.mdc`)
4. Composition/sections guides

